{"id":12267,"title":"Neuroethics and animals: methods and philosophy.","abstract":"This article provides an overview of the six other contributions in the Neuroethics and Animals special section. In addition, it discusses the methodological and theoretical problems of interdisciplinary fields. The article suggests that interdisciplinary approaches without established methodological and theoretical bases are difficult to assess scientifically. This might cause these fields to expand without actually advancing. ","date":"2014-02-18","categories":"Animal Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24534740","annotations":[{"name":"Interdisciplinarity","weight":0.703461,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interdisciplinarity"},{"name":"Science","weight":0.685739,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Science"},{"name":"Medicine","weight":0.654651,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medicine"},{"name":"Philosophy","weight":0.613397,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philosophy"},{"name":"Methodology","weight":0.606559,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Methodology"},{"name":"Theory","weight":0.599129,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Theory"},{"name":"Animal","weight":0.0604754,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Animal"},{"name":"Neuroethics","weight":0.0311921,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neuroethics"},{"name":"Minimal Supersymmetric Standard Model","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minimal_Supersymmetric_Standard_Model"},{"name":"Base (chemistry)","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Base_(chemistry)"}]}
